        "title": "Mastering Version Release",
        "excerpt":"ğŸš€ How to Edit This Website     ğŸ“‹ BEFORE EDITING   1ï¸âƒ£ Sync with Deployed App  Ensure your local repository is up-to-date with the deployed version:  cd miftah-ahmad-choiri.origin.io git pull origin deploy   2ï¸âƒ£ Create a New Branch  Switch to a new branch named develop:  git branch -M develop   3ï¸âƒ£ Check Current Version Tag  Verify the current version tag before making changes:  git tag  If no tags exist, create an initial version tag:  git tag -a v0.1.0 -m \"Releasing version 0.1.0\" git tag  Example Output:  v0.1.0   4ï¸âƒ£ Create a New Tag for the Upgrade  Tag the repository for the new version and push it to the remote:  git tag -a v0.1.1 -m \"Releasing version 0.1.1\" git push origin v0.1.1 git tag  Example Output:  v0.1.0 v0.1.1     ğŸ’» DEVELOPING SOFTWARE   To run the website in local mode with auto-reload  bundle exec jekyll serve --livereload --force_polling --watch   Make changes, track modifications, and commit your updates:  git status git add . git commit -m \"Create new features or fix code\" git push -u origin develop     ğŸš€ AFTER EDITING   ğŸ“¦ Publish a New Release  Authenticate with GitHub CLI and create a new release:  gh auth login gh release list gh release create v0.1.1 --title \"Release v0.1.1\" --notes \"Create new feature and fix code\" gh release list # check on the remote repository for branch develop   ğŸ”„ Update Release after Changes  If you make any changes after the release published, you need to do following update  gh release view v0.1.1 git tag -d v0.1.1 git tag -a v0.1.1 -m \"Final adding new Markdown file how to edit this software and how to release a new version code. And update release v0.1.1\" git push origin develop --force  After update the tag, you can update the github release  gh release view v0.1.1 gh release edit v0.1.1 --notes \"Final adding new Markdown file how to edit this software and how to release a new version code. And update release v0.1.1\"   ğŸ’¾ Merge branch develop with branch deploy &amp; main  Merge changes into deploy and main  # checkout into deploy and merge git checkout deploy git merge develop git push origin deploy  Backup the deployed script into main branch  git checkout main git merge deploy git push origin main   ğŸš® Delete develop branch  Delete branch develop, so you can start fresh in the next update  git branch -d develop git push origin --delete develop     âœ… All done! Your changes have been successfully committed and released. ğŸ‰ ```   This version includes:     Emojis for better visual separation.   Clear section headings with descriptive titles.   Consistent code formatting.   Dividers (---) for clean transitions between sections.   Let me know if youâ€™d like further tweaks! ğŸš€  ","categories": [],
