        "title": "How to Edit Jekyll",
        "excerpt":"Whatâ€™s New in Release v0.1.2   Directory Edited on v0.1.2  List of directories that were edited:     ğŸ—‚ï¸ _data   ğŸ—‚ï¸ _docs   ğŸ—‚ï¸ _pages   ğŸ—‚ï¸ _posts   ğŸ“‚ assets   ğŸ“‚ release-notes   ğŸ“„ _index.md   ğŸ”§ _config.yml     1. ğŸ—‚ï¸ _data  Adding an author on the page  Add an author by inserting it into the following section, then go to _pages to add the author on the pages.   # Site Author Miftah Ahmad Choiri:   #### &lt;&lt;&lt; Create new author here ####   name             : Miftah Ahmad Choiri # *name is a YAML reference pointing to the &amp;anchor earlier   avatar           : \"/assets/images/myprofile1.png\"   bio              : \"Miftah Ahmad Choiri ...\"   location         : \"Jakarta, ID\"   links:     - label: \"Resume/CV\"       icon: \"fas fa-fw fa-link\"       url: \"https://miftah-ahmad-choiri.github.io/\"   Add the author here in _pages/year-archive.md:   --- title: \"Posts by Year\" permalink: /year-archive/ layout: posts author: Miftah Ahmad Choiri    #### &lt;&lt;&lt; Add author here #### author_profile: true ---   Edit Navigation Sidebar  You can edit the navigation sidebar in _data/navigation.yml.   # documentation links docs:   - title: Getting Started     children:       - title: \"Tutorial\"      #### &lt;&lt;&lt; Add title on navigation ####         url: /docs/tutorial/   #### &lt;&lt;&lt; Add URL link here ####   Make sure the permalink is also updated in _docs/3.tutorial.md.   --- title: \"Tutorial\"              #### &lt;&lt;&lt; Edit title on document #### permalink: /docs/tutorial/     #### &lt;&lt;&lt; Edit permalink to point to URL #### ---    2. ğŸ—‚ï¸ _docs  Edit the documentation name, link URL, and navigation link  You can edit documentation files. In this case, we edited _docs/03-installation.md into _docs/tutorial.md. The file name changes from â€œInstallationâ€ into â€œTutorialâ€ and the permalink changes.   Before:   --- title: \"Installation\"           #### &lt;&lt;&lt; Edit title on document #### permalink: /docs/installation/  #### &lt;&lt;&lt; Edit permalink to point to URL #### ---   After:   --- title: \"Tutorial\"                #### &lt;&lt;&lt; Edit title on document #### permalink: /docs/tutorial/       #### &lt;&lt;&lt; Edit permalink to point to URL #### ---   Also, ensure the sidebar is updated in _data/navigation.yml.   # documentation links docs:   - title: Getting Started     children:       - title: \"Tutorial\"       #### &lt;&lt;&lt; Add title on navigation ####         url: /docs/tutorial/    #### &lt;&lt;&lt; Add URL link here ####   3. ğŸ—‚ï¸ _pages  Add author on the pages layout  Here, you can add author information in the _pages/year-archive.md.   --- title: \"Posts by Year\" permalink: /year-archive/ layout: posts author: Miftah Ahmad Choiri    #### &lt;&lt;&lt; Add author here ####  author_profile: true           #### &lt;&lt;&lt; Add author here #### ---   4. ğŸ—‚ï¸ _posts  Create new posts  You can create new posts by creating a markdown file in _posts/2024-04-18-welcome-to-miftah.md. Donâ€™t forget to use the date format 2024-04-18-xxxxx.md to ensure the post appears at the top.   --- title: \"Welcome Miftah!\" date: 2019-04-18T15:34:30-04:00 categories:   - blog tags:   - Jekyll   - update ---  Hi, Miftah...   5. ğŸ“‚ assets  Add images and store in the images directory  You can add new images and create new directories within the assets folder to make it easier to manage and use images. â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”  6. ğŸ“‚ release-notes  Update any notes/documentation for each change  Please take note of every change you make to ensure everything is trackable. â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”-  7. ğŸ“„ _index.md  Change the homepage of the website  You can change the homepage of the website by editing the index.md.   --- layout: splash permalink: / hidden: true header:   overlay_color: \"#5e616c\"   overlay_image: /assets/images/mm-home-page-feature.jpg   actions:     - label: \"&lt;i class='fas fa-download'&gt;&lt;/i&gt; Install now\"       url: \"/docs/quick-start-guide/\" excerpt: &gt;   A flexible two-column Jekyll theme. Perfect for building personal sites, blogs, and portfolios.&lt;br /&gt;   &lt;small&gt;&lt;a href=\"https://github.com/mmistakes/minimal-mistakes/releases/tag/4.26.2\"&gt;Latest release v4.26.2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/small&gt; feature_row:   - image_path: /assets/images/mm-customizable-feature.png     alt: \"customizable\"     title: \"Super customizable\"     excerpt: \"Everything from the menus, sidebars, comments, and more can be configured or set with YAML Front Matter.\"     url: \"/docs/configuration/\"     btn_class: \"btn--primary\"     btn_label: \"Learn more\"   - image_path: /assets/images/mm-responsive-feature.png     alt: \"fully responsive\"     title: \"Responsive layouts\"     excerpt: \"Built with HTML5 + CSS3. All layouts are fully responsive with helpers to augment your content.\"     url: \"/docs/layouts/\"     btn_class: \"btn--primary\"     btn_label: \"Learn more\"   - image_path: /assets/images/mm-free-feature.png     alt: \"100% free\"     title: \"100% free\"     excerpt: \"Free to use however you want under the MIT License. Clone it, fork it, customize it... whatever!\"     url: \"/docs/license/\"     btn_class: \"btn--primary\"     btn_label: \"Learn more\"       ---   &lt;div class=\"feature__wrapper\"&gt;      &lt;/div&gt;    8. ğŸ”§ _config.yml  Add a logo on the website  You can change the logo of the website by editing _config.yml.   logo                     : \"/assets/myimages/logo.png\"  ","categories": [],
